This template displays discharge measurement units used within various [[:Category:Geobox]] templates, automatically converting between metric/imperial values. The input must be unformatted numeric values (i.e. without commas, the commas are automatically added to the output).

It can display and convert following units:
* '''kg''' to '''lb''' ('''kilograms''' to '''pounds''') and vice-versa

The template has 3 unnamed parameters: <code><nowiki>{{Unit weight| unit| value| round}}</nowiki></code>. Their meaning is as follows: 
# '''unit''' … obligatory, unit (<code>kg, lb</code>) of parameter <code><nowiki>value</nowiki></code>, it will get displayed first
# '''value''' … obligatory, numerical value
# '''round''' … mandatory, number of decimal digits (negative numbers can be used for rounded figures); if not specified 0 is assumed

For examples see [[Template_talk:Unit_weight|discussion]].

